Definition: A code that connects the entry to a security policy. Security labels can be updated when the resource changes, or whenever the security sub-system chooses to.

Short: Code representing a code that connects the entry to a security policy. Security labels can be updated when the resource changes, or whenever the security sub-system chooses to.
